Greetings to Yemeni President 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Ali Abdullah Saleh on Sept. 25 on the occasion of the 38th anniversary of the Yemeni revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He in the message extended warm congratulations to the President, government and people of Yemen on the revolution day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Wishing the President and people of Yemen successes in their work for the prosperity of the country, he expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms.

North side's delegation to inter-Korean ministerial talks leaves 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The north side's delegation led by Jon Kum Jin, senior councilor of the DPRK cabinet, left here to attend the third round of the inter-Korean ministerial talks due in Jeju Island. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was seen off at the airport by Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su, director of the secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland An Kyong Ho and officials concerned.

Nigerian embassy officials assist motorway construction site 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Nigerian ambassador to Korea Alhaji Daudu Sulaiman and embassy officials Tuesday assisted the construction site of the Pyongyang-Nampho Motorway. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They were told about achievements of constructors and gave their great impressions, looking round the construction site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They handed over aid materials and encouraged constructors in their work, working with them.

Talks held between Korean and German FMs 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Talks were held between Paek Nam Sun, Foreign Minister of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, and Oskar Fischer, Foreign Minister of the Federal Republic of Germany, in Berlin on September 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the talks the recent situation on the Korean peninsula and the north-south dialogue were affirmatively appreciated and views on the development of the bilateral relations between the two countries were exchanged.

Papers observe World Day of Tourism 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- Papers today dedicate articles to the World Day of Tourism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Rodong Sinmun in an article says that multifarious international functions have been held to mark the day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The third general meeting of the world tourism organization held in Spain in September 1979 set Sept. 27 as world day of tourism and decided to mark the day from 1980, the paper says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK became a member state of the organization in 1987. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This year's slogan set forth by the organization is "Techniques and nature: Two major tasks for tourism in early 21st century." Under this slogan member states of the organization are conducting brisk tourist activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK is taking an active part in the international tourist activities and making strenuous efforts to develop tourism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Tourists from many countries visit the DPRK every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minju Joson says that entertainment and rest grounds and scenic spots wonderfully arranged in many places of the country are greatly helpful to the people's cultural and emotional life.

Russian political party leader on Putin's Korea visit 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The Russian newspaper Patriot no. 33 carried what Oleg Shenin, chairman of the council of the Union of Communist Parties--the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, said as regards President Putin's Korea visit at a press conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He affirmatively appreciated Putin's Korea visit, which he said shows that Russia is interested in socialist Korea firmly pursuing independent policies with self-reliance under the guidance of its leader Kim Jong Il and the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Putin's visit clearly proves that the authority of the DPRK which is making great achievements by applying socialist principles, confidently advancing along the road of socialism, is rising day by day. In other words, it is the exploit of the people and party of Korea and its leader Kim Jong Il, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Our party pays deep concern to the measures taken by the DPRK for peaceful reunification of the country. Experience of Korea will be beneficial to our struggle to revive the soviet union.

U.S. attempt to keep its troops in South Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- U.S. Secretary of Defense Cohen, when he separately met with the Minister of Foreign Affairs and the Director General of the Defense Agency of Japan, said that the improvement of relations between the north and south of Korea is progressing apace but the military capability of North Korea has not weakened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And he said that though reconciliation and even reunification between the north and the south are achieved, it is important to keep the U.S. troops on the Korean peninsula and that the military balance should be maintained in this region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Japan agreed with this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Commenting on this fact, Rodong Sinmun today says the absurd remarks came when the world peace-loving people are loudly calling for the U.S. troops' pullout from South Korea as the north-south reconciliation is rapidly developing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The news analyst commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S. claim for the maintenance "of military balance" is aimed at describing the U.S. troops as "war deterrent force" and keeping them in South Korea for an indefinite period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In order to dominate the world it is imperative to take hold on the Asia-Pacific region by force of arms and, to this end, it is important to turn the whole of Korea into a stronghold of aggression. This is the U.S. calculation and policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   That is why the United States is desperately obstructing the Korean nation from taking the road of reconciliation, unity and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are very proud of the fact that they have strengthened the self-reliant defense capability in every way to cope with the U.S. moves against the DPRK, the commentary says, refuting Cohen's assertion on the military capability of North Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that the north and the south agreed to independently solve the issue of national reunification by concerted efforts of the Korean nation, its master, it stresses that the United States must abandon its anachronistic Korea policy and the design to permanently occupy South Korea and go home at an early date, swimming with the changing trend of the Korean peninsula toward reconciliation.

Supreme incarnation of devotedly safeguarding leader 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- "The first generation of the Korean revolution fought like phoenix and won victory in their struggle to defend the President Kim Il Sung in hearty response to the slogan let us defend the headquarters with our lives  put up by Kim Jong Suk, the heroine of Mt. Paektu, during the rigorous anti-Japanese armed struggle. Kim Jong Suk was, indeed, the  supreme incarnation who devotedly safeguarded the leader."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is what Hwang Sun Hui, an anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter, said retrospecting the noble revolutionary spirit and indomitable fighting trait of Kim Jong Suk during the anti-Japanese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The noble life of Kim Jong Suk, an indomitable communist revolutionary fighter and an anti-Japanese heroine, was consistent with the spirit of devotedly safeguarding the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She joined the revolutionary struggle in her early years and set a brilliant example in the most rigorous and hard-fought anti-Japanese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In June Juche 29 (1940) she safeguarded the great commander Kim Il Sung as a human shield when a critical situation was created in a battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her fighting spirit and trait were highly displayed in the life-and-death battle sites and everywhere she went for underground activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After the liberation of the country, she energetically worked for the well-being of the President and to fulfil his line for nation-building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After triumphant return home she postponed visiting her native home within a hailing distance and  upheld the leadership of the President giving on-site guidance to hundreds of units across the country until the last moments of her life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her spirit of devotedly safeguarding the leader is fully reflected in the slogan "Let us defend with our lives the headquarters of revolution headed by the great comrade Kim Jong Il "&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean people are devotedly safeguarding Kim Jong Il  and pushing ahead with a grand forward advance for the building of a powerful nation upholding the slogan representing her noble intention.

Kim Jong Il's work published abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- A famous work of General Secretary Kim Jong Il "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation" was published in booklet by the Sikeria Publishing House of Sweden on September 23 on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the Worker's Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Expounded in the work are the immortal feats the President Kim Il Sung performed for the unity of the Korean nation by putting forward the idea of the Juche-oriented great national unity and the principles and ways of achieving great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The director of the publishing house said he is convinced that Korea's reunification would be surely achieved according to the proposal of Kim Il Sung for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo and the idea of Kim Jong Il on great national unity.

"My Impressions of DPRK" published in Guyana 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- "My Impressions of the DPRK" written by Robert Williams, general secretary of the Good Green Guyana, was published in booklet in Guyana on September 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The book consists of the first chapter "the Grand People's Study House", the second chapter "Mt. Myohyang" and the third chapter "Kim Il Sung, He Is the Great Leader of the Korean People and the Eternal President". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The first chapter refers to the unremitting efforts and warm love of the President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il who had the Grand People's Study House built. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The second chapter describes the brilliant feats of Kim Jong Il who had the international friendship exhibition built fine and has wisely led people to glorify the greatness of the President for all ages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The third chapter elaborates on the glorious revolutionary activities and immortal feats of the President, who is revered by all the Korean people and the peaceloving people of the world. It says that though he passed away, he will always live in the hearts of the peaceloving people of the world for his immortal feats performed for the era and the revolution.

First home-visiting group of Chongryon compatriots meet with their families 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seoul, September 25 (KNS-KCNA) -- Members of the first home-visiting group of compatriots under the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) visited their hometowns, had emotional meetings with their families and relatives from whom they were parted and visited their ancestral tombs from September 23 to 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They met with their families and relatives at their homes in Seoul and localities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They inquired each other after their kinsmen's health and exchanged tidings, sharing board and room with their families and relatives in a homelike atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They told stories that they have been true to patriotic faith and principle even under difficult and complicated circumstances in Japan, an alien land, regarding the great leaders Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il as a mental pillar, built organizations of all levels and schools in various places where the compatriots live, firmly rallied around Chongryon, and the situation of national reunification is favourably changing following the historic Pyongyang meeting and the adoption of the north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They also visited tombs of their parents at their home-villages.
